definition.value: This is an AE which refers to the larynx and feel discomfortable.
This is an AE which is manifested by obstructive breathing patterns reflecting functional or mechanical upper airway obstruction.
This is an AE which is a feeling on the laryngeal of not being able to breathe well enough.
This is an AE which is redness of the laryngeal skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.
This is an AE which is the increase in the volume of laryngeal tissue due to the enlargement of its component cells.

This is an AE which may be a cause of ABD in preterm newborns and it may arise from oesophageal reflux and/or presence of the feeding tube. It can be diagnosed by atraumatic fiberoptic fibroscopy and successfully treated with corticosteroids.
This is an AE which is a distressing laryngeal  feeling often caused by intense or damaging stimuli.
This is an AE which is a rare medical condition in which benign tumors (papilloma) form along the aerodigestive tract.
This is an AE which is a complex disorder of intralaryngeal and extralaryngeal movement.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the larynx (voice box) and is allergic.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the larynx (voice box) caused by bacterial.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the larynx (voice box) caused by viral.
This is an AE which is the most common cause of chronic stridor in infancy, in which the soft, immature cartilage of the upper larynx collapses inward during inhalation, causing airway obstruction.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the laryngotracheal tissue.
This is an AE which is a larynx state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.

This is an AE which is the enlargement and failure of the right ventricle of the heart as a response to increased vascular resistance (such as from pulmonic stenosis) or high blood pressure in the lungs.

This is an AE which is the enlargement and failure of the right ventricle of the heart as a response to increased vascular resistance (such as from pulmonic stenosis) or high blood pressure in the lungs and is acute.
This is an AE which results in right ventricular hypertrophy (RVH), whereas acute pulmonary heart disease usually results in dilatation.

This is an AE which is an abnormal pattern of breathing characterized by progressively deeper, and sometimes faster, breathing followed by a gradual decrease that results in a temporary stop in breathing called an apnea.
This is an AE which is a malignant lung tumor characterized by uncontrolled cell growth in tissues of the lung.
This is an AE which is a passage or airway in the respiratory system that conducts air into the lungs and its function becomes disorder.
This is an AE which is a state characterised by easily triggered bronchospasm (contraction of the bronchioles or small airways).
This is an AE which is a bronchial state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.
This is an AE which is a radiologic sign which occurs when excess fluid or mucus buildup in the small airway passages of the lung causes localized patches of atelectasis (lung collapse).
This is an AE which is a disease in which there is permanent enlargement of parts of the airways of the lung.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the bronchi (large and medium-sized airways) in the lungs that causes coughing.
This is an AE which is short-term bronchitis – inflammation of the bronchi (large and medium-sized airways) of the lungs.
This is an AE which is inflammation  caused by bacterial of the bronchi (large and medium-sized airways) in the lungs that causes coughing.
This is an AE which is a lower respiratory tract disease, defined by a productive cough that lasts for three months or more per year for at least two years.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the bronchi (large and medium-sized airways) in the lungs that causes coughing because pneumococcal infection.
This is an AE which is short term inflammation of the bronchi of the lungs and the cause is a viral infection.
This is an AE which is a term for weak cartilage in the walls of the bronchial tubes, often occurring in children under a day.
This is an AE which is a chronic lung disease in which premature infants, usually those who were treated with supplemental oxygen, require long-term oxygen.
This is an AE which is a known complication of endobronchial tuberculosis though most patients with endobronchial stenosis do not develop severe bronchostenosis or occlusion.
This is an AE which is abnormally slow breathing.
This is an AE which is a mass of cells (tumor) that lacks the ability to either invade neighboring tissue or metastasize (spread throughout the body) such as benign lung neoplasm.
This is an AE which is the cessation of breathing.
This is an AE which is a sleep disorder in which abnormalities in breathing occur during sleep that may or may not be present while awake.
This is an AE which is the partial or complete wasting away of a part of the vocal cord.

This is an AE which is a pathology affecting the vocal folds (commonly referred to as the vocal cords)characterized by full or partial vocal fold closure causing difficulty and distress during respiration, especially during inhalation.
This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of vocal cord  tissues to harmful stimuli.
This is an AE which is an injury to one or both recurrent laryngeal nerves (RLNs), which control all muscles of the larynx except for the cricothyroid muscle.
This is an AE which is an injury to one or both recurrent laryngeal nerves (RLNs), which control all muscles of the larynx except for the cricothyroid muscle.
This is an AE which is bilaterally symmetrical benign white masses that form at the midpoint of the vocal folds.

label.value: upper respiratory tract infection bacterial AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is an illness caused by an acute bacterial  infection, which involves the upper respiratory tract, including the nose, sinuses, pharynx, larynx or trachea.
This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of body tissues to harmful stimuli such as upper respiratory tract inflammation.
This is an AE which is a upper respiratory tract state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.
This is an AE which occurs when excessive mucus is produced by the nasal mucosa.

label.value: viral upper respiratory tract infection AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is an illness caused by an acute viral  infection, which involves the upper respiratory tract, including the nose, sinuses, pharynx, larynx or trachea.
This is an AE which is pathological conditions affecting the organs and tissues that make gas exchange difficult in air-breathing animals and is allergic.
